  "chapter": {
    "number": 27,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Do Not Boast about Tomorrow"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not boast about tomorrow,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for you do not know what a day may bring.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let another praise you, and not your own mouth—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a stranger, and not your own lips.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A stone is heavy and sand is a burden,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but aggravation from a fool outweighs them both.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wrath is cruel and anger is like a flood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but who can withstand jealousy?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better an open rebuke",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than love that is concealed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wounds of a friend are faithful,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the kisses of an enemy are deceitful.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The soul that is full loathes honey,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but to a hungry soul, any bitter thing is sweet.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a bird that strays from its nest",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a man who wanders from his home.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Oil and incense bring joy to the heart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the sweetness of a friend is counsel to the soul.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not forsake your friend or your father’s friend,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and do not go to your brother’s house",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in the day of your calamity;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "better a neighbor nearby",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than a brother far away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be wise, my son, and bring joy to my heart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that I can answer him who taunts me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The prudent see danger and take cover;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the simple keep going and pay the penalty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Take the garment of him who posts security for a stranger;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "get collateral if it is for a foreigner.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4259
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If one blesses his neighbor with a loud voice early in the morning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will be counted to him as a curse.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A constant dripping on a rainy day",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a contentious woman are alike—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "restraining her is like holding back the wind",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or grasping oil with one’s right hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As iron sharpens iron,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so one man sharpens another.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4260
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever tends a fig tree will eat its fruit,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he who looks after his master will be honored.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As water reflects the face,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the heart reflects the true man.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sheol and Abaddon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4261
          },
          {
            "text": "are never satisfied;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the eyes of man are never satisfied.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A crucible for silver and a furnace for gold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a man is tested by the praise accorded him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though you grind a fool like grain with mortar and a pestle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet his folly will not depart from him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be sure to know the state of your flocks,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pay close attention to your herds;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "for riches are not forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor does a crown endure to every generation.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When hay is removed and new growth appears",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the grain from the hills is gathered,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the lambs will provide you with clothing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the goats with the price of a field.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will have plenty of goats’ milk to feed you—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "food for your household",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and nourishment for your maidservants.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
